Last night we went there not knowing that Ibrahim was off for the evening. Many guests sat at the bar with empty glasses and hadn't even been offered a menu. The manager just stood there and watched her staff "drowned". She was "too cute" to assist them in any way. There are too many restaurants in New York for Applebees to treat their customers so poorly. If they don't get it together, on to the next one.
Processed_Feedback: manager service mediocre night evening guest bar glass manager way restaurant applebee customer

Author: Jeff Randall
Feedback: Haven't been in a while.  It didn't start well.  We were seated and then ignored for some time.  Once they realized we were there, service improved greatly.  I had the orange chicken incredibowl and the wife had an alfredo dish.  We both felt our dishes were excellent, with the wife commenting that she felt the alfredo was better than Olive Garden's which is high praise indeed from her.  To top things off they kindly, and without prompting, comped me the incredibowl because of the issues when we first arrived.  Not much in the way of atmosphere, but they are in the middle of a remodel, so can't fault them that.  Ended up being a good experience.  Update:. Went back to try something other than the incredi-bowls and ended up being served the worst meal we had ever had in our lives.  Indescribably bad.  Had the riblets and couldn't identify the animal the ribs came from.  Might have been aardvark.  Didn't eat half of it and when done, covered the plate with a napkin like the crime scene it was .  Wasn't worth taking home to the dogs. Wife's steak was awful to.  Cold with congealed fat floating on top.  Shudder just thinking about it.  Won't be back.
Processed_Feedback: incredibowl wife praise thing incredibowl issue way experience update bowl meal life riblet rib plate crime scene shudder

Author: Richard Pendergast
Feedback: Entered Applebees and stood there waiting on a hostess to be seated.  Everyone seemed to be ignoring us, so eventually we seated ourselves.  The place was not busy.  And, several groups after us had the same issue.   They went to the bar.  When the hostess realized that we seated ourselves, she seemed angry and huffed off.  Eventually our waitress realized that she had another table of customers and gave us menus and took our orders.  The food was excellent, the waitress was good.  But, I think that I now understand  why Applebees parking lot is mostly empty and the nearby CrackerBarrel's parking lot is always full.
Processed_Feedback: place group issue bar hostess waitress table customer food applebee parking lot parking lot

Feedback: My wife and I went to the restaurant last night in a really bad way. We had broken down on the highway and had just gotten towed into the local car dealership for service. Frankie and his staff got wind of our predicament and bent over backwards to make us a little more comfortable while we explored ways to turn things back around. I had a burger and fries while my son had a cheese pizza and the other individual with me had a chicken quesadilla salad. The burger was a little overdone, but the flavor was great. The salad got good reviews and the pizza was a cheap microwave cheese pizza. Overall, it was a decent- priced meal and good service. The thing that got me a bit was the sticky floor throughout the restaurant. Everything was clean and the restaurant smelled clean. I'm not sure if they used too much cleaner or the wrong type, but I left thinking about their sticky floor. Great service and I'd eat there again.

Author: Bille Baty
Feedback:
Had a great server named, Chad, who really amplified this positive experience to Applebee's. There was no wait and a really nice seat right by a huge window.

The salad was wonderful & Chad made sure the cucumber was removed from mine. He let us know about a great deal on an appetizer which was incredible. Now, I eat Mexican food several times each week but this Chips & Queso appetizer was surprisingly good. Chad even brought fresh jalapeños for my wife.

Now for the steaks, mine was cooked exactly as I ordered it, and my wife's was exactly how she ordered it. I can't tell you how many times I've had to send her steak back to the kitchen over the years. WELL DONE is difficult, I know, due to customers complaining about a dry steak, but hers was perfect. Cudos to the cook.

My only complaint was the BLONDIE dessert is no longer Maple-Walnut. But the new variation is still a delicious dessert.

Be sure to ask for Chad if he's available.
Processed_Feedback: server experience applebee seat window salad deal food time week chip wife time year customer steak complaint variation dessert

Author: Lynn Bauer
Feedback:
The closest Applebee's to my home is a 20 minute drive. I was able to walk a short distance from the Hampton Inn where I'm staying. But there's plenty of parking if you're driving.

The curbside pickup is on the west side of the building.

I was seated immediately by the hostess at a booth which I requested.
The server was friendly, polite, and professional and took my order a short while after I was seated.

When I ordered the Strawberry Margarita, I did not expect a super big one. I could actually taste the Malibu Rum in it. The picture looked refreshing and it was. The server also brought a large glass of ice water, as some margaritas can be super sweet. Although I like a more tequila in my margaritas, this was refreshing and the coconut flavor popped.

My huge Oriental Chicken Salad with crispy chicken was delicious and they didn't skimp on the dressing. It was served with a hot, buttery, herb breadstick which was a nice touch. I do miss the mandarin oranges the salad used to come with decades ago. I left with enough salad to be served as a side with another meal.

When I arrived, the restaurant was moderately full. When I left, the place was packed.

The reason I knocked a star off was that the leatherette seat of the booth was cracked and peeling and should be replaced.  And, there was something about the size of a dime and orange stuck to the table.

Otherwise, I thoroughly enjoyed my dining experience at Applebee's.
Processed_Feedback: home minute drive distance parking pickup side booth server order rum picture server glass ice water coconut chicken salad buttery herb breadstick touch salad decade salad side meal restaurant place reason booth size dime table dining experience

My wife ribs and baked potato must have been sitting under the hot lamp for a good 20 min waiting on the rest of our food. Everything else was fantastic. The server was friendly and helpful. Author: D Miller
Feedback:
I love this Applebee's! I always get the half off appetizers. Went there with my mom, less than $15 to feed two people wings + quesadillas + fries. Staff is always friendly and meet your needs.

For instance, I called about a to-go order and realised it wasn't half off then continued to rearannge my order to make it more affordable. The guy on the phone walked me through the process and gave me a smile when I came to pick up! If that were me I would have definitely rolled my eyes while on the phone, lol. I ended up tipping him a $5.

Another time I had brought in my own food one night and the waitress did not say anything to me about it. She did jokingly suggest I leave the resteraunt but it was nice that I had the privilege to eat my own food inside.

My only complaint is that they charge you for condiments, like sour cream, and don't tell you when you order. It's not worth excluding an extra star though.

Probably going to be seen here within the next week�.

Author: Stacey Wilson
Feedback:
4 out of 5, because of ...
The Power of Customer Service (Read All for accurate review)

We arrived at Applebee's and waited to be seated, it took a bit of time, but we waited and the hostess saw us and seated us. It wasn't that busy, but for the late evening hours it was probably a lot for the number of staff on. We came in and were followed by about 4 other tables as we waited 20 minutes to be greeted and  served. Now I always try to be patient and put myself in their shoes; but as we saw not 1, not 2, but all 4 tables that came in after us be greeted and served before us. Patience was beginning to wear thin. I can understand you being busy, I can even understand not knowing who came in first when it was similar times (as the first table came in at almost the exact time), but that 4th table was in the last minute of the 20 minute wait and was greeted within 60 seconds of sitting down. So I told my husband, I need to get something out of the car and we would allow them about 2 more minutes, and to order everything if they came by. As I re-entered the restaurant, a man who I assume was the manager greeted me. I explained, I didn't need to be seated, as I was seated 20 minutes ago and waiting on a server. He promptly asked if he could be our server and did so in an ABSOLUTELY WONDERFUL manner.
He immediately took our entire order, got us drinks, and offered to comp the check, BUT here is the point I want to make. He did such a fantastic job, I felt no NEED for the check to be comped. So we happily paid the bill AND tipped this man. He truly deserved it. I hope Applebee's appreciates THIS man. If I owned a large company, I would want a man like this running things. I only regret not getting his name. As I am not sure if the name on my receipt is his. Poor oversight on my part. I was tired, but thanks to this man, not hungry and hunting for another place to eat!!
Processed_Feedback: service review applebee bit time hostess evening hour lot number staff table minute patient shoe table patience time table time table minute minute husband car restaurant man minute order drink check point job need check company man name receipt oversight part man place

Author: Imani Davis
Feedback:
Went at about 9pm for a quick meal. It was a 20 minute wait while there was visible seating, a server came after about 15 minutes to let us know her table was being cleaned. Finally the host came to seat us in another section and explained he was the only host and apologized but still no explanation of why the wait was so long to be seated. The waitress was pleasant but seemed to be a bit overwhelmed. A 5 minute wait to order drinks. Waited another 10 minutes for soggy lemons for water. The food was mediocre at best and overly salted. They also no longer have a veggie burger. We stuck to basics like classic burger, house salad, chicken tenders and Alfredo. Ordered a drink( long island) which did not come out until after the check and was made to go because the bartender "cut himself" and she had to find the backup bartender. This was honestly one of the worst dining experiences I have ever had. Food definitely not photo worthy.

Edit: Returned to visit on 7/23 and could tell the difference. Staff was very friendly and was quickly informed of the wait time. Drinks and apps came so fast and the waitress Taquana was awesome!!! Food was pretty decent. I was so pleased I decided to give them another try. I am glad to have a much better dining experience than before.
Engagement Response: I am sorry about what happened with your visit and would like to hear more. If you could reach out to me at todd.cummings@therosegroup.com or at 215-579-9220 ext. 1701 with your name and email or phone number, I’d like to hear more about your experience.

Author: Richard Dickson
Feedback:
This is a positive, but honest review.

Kudos for handling a miscommunication well. Upon entering we were warned of an extreme wait although many seats appeared available. However, our wait was very reasonable.

When taken to our seat, we had to wait for the table and the seats to be cleaned.

Our order was taken in a reasonable amount of time. And, the food was also delivered in a satisfactory amount of time.

The food looked good and tasted good.

Here the miscommunication began. Under the Ribs Section of the menu, they list both riblets and ribs. I ordered the smaller plate of the riblets. I know that I specifically mentioned the price and I feel sure I pointed out the item and price on the menu.

Since it's been so long since I ate at Applebee's, I didn't notice a discrepancy between what I ordered and what was delivered. The fries were very good and the meat was tender and tasty. There was some dryness in the thicker pieces of meat and the edges.

When the ticket was delivered I noticed a higher price for my meal. Looking at a menu still on the table I noticed it was the price of the small plate of ribs. After calling it to the attention of the server, she assured me that she had entered it correctly and that they would fix it.

Then a manager came out to explain that what I had eaten was the item that was charged. I continued to explain that regardless it was not the item ordered. However, I suggested that since it was what had been delivered and consumed, that we would pay the higher price.

Here the restaurant via the manager stepped up and adjusted the price to the item ordered and not the item delivered. Kudos!

So, although there were some issues, I would eat at this restaurant again. And, I would recommend it to others.
Processed_Feedback: review seat seat table seat order amount time food amount time food rib plate riblet price item meat piece meat edge ticket price meal menu table price plate rib attention server manager item item price restaurant manager price item item restaurant

Author: Daniel Reichard
Feedback: I'll start off saying that the cook and I must have pretty different opinions on how a "rare" steak is cooked, but the steak did taste good even so and beyond that, was very tender for being overdone.  The mashed potatoes were also really good.  The garlicky green beans were sort of flavorless to me.  The prices per portion sizes are really high in my opinion, you can get bigger, better steaks at a real steakhouse for the same cost, but they do offer pretty decent 2 for 20 deals for a quick bite.  I do think that if steaks are sold at steak house prices, they should be steak house quality including if you ask "how would you like that cooked?", and are told "rare" Cook to order and not arbitrarily just make it what I'm guessing is between medium and medium well.
Processed_Feedback: opinion potato bean flavorless price portion size opinion steakhouse cost deal bite house price quality cook order medium

Author: HeidiAnn Geiger
Feedback:
Applebee's of Painted Post is a eating establishment with many choices. The appetizer was done well. Our server was pleasant and experienced. The dining room was clean.
The dinner left something to be desired, though. One steak was supposed to be medium, but bled on the plate. The other was ordered medium well and was red in the middle. The potatoes were fine, but the broccoli was almost raw and all but the florets was inedible.
It's might be good as a bar, but the food quality isn't very good.
It was our second time going to Applebee's, and probably our last.
Processed_Feedback: establishment choice dining room dinner plate bar food quality time
